articles.description:
Inflationistas literally going to wait until YoY inflation is negative before declaring victory aren’t they

Peter Schiff: A one-month, .1% dip in #CPI doesn't mean #inflation is cooling off. The core was up .3%, which annualizes to 4%, double the #Fed's 2% target. YoY CPI still rose 6.5% and with the dollar weakening, federal budget deficits & consumer credit soaring, inflation is poised to heat up.

RT Doug Colkitt (🐊,🐊)
After today's print, inflation in the second half of 2022 was officially lower than inflation in the second half of 2019. (And below the Fed's 2% target)

Doug Colkitt (🐊,🐊): Just eyeballing the CPI MoM chart, it seems very unlikely we get a hot reading (e.g. over 0.5%). 
Inflation really does look like it crescendoed in the first half of 2022. The past six months basically look like we returned to a pre-pandemic regime.
